{"TopicId":205887,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"More fine tuning or direct number imput to ajust thrust slider on boosters","CreatedByName":"El Globo","CreatedById":217813,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-07T10:34:51Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"El Globo","CreatedById":217813,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-07T10:34:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nHi,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nWhen I want to adjust the thrust sliders,\u00A0 the only actual way is to move the button\u00A0 and try to get the desired value \u0022say : 70%.\u0022 When you want to do the same for 6 boosters, most of the time the slider will go to 69.5 or 71.5 and you waste time trying to adjust it perfectly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nPlease correct the way you do it, by example with allowing us to set a direct imput number value, and enable the slider to glue\u0022 the value by increment of 0.5%\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jimmymcgoochie","CreatedById":199902,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-07T15:58:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou already can- click the # button on the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Part Action Window\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Part Action Window\u0022\u003EPAW\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and it switches to typing mode where you can type in the numbers you want.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-12-07T15:59:04Z\u0022 title=\u002212/07/2021 03:59  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 7, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by jimmymcgoochie\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"El Globo","CreatedById":217813,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-08T08:17:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-content